
1. The *.fa files were the whole chloroplast genomes of Nicotiana genus.
2. The correspondence between species names and accession numbers can be found in Table 1 of the article 'Comparative chloroplast genomes of Nicotiana species (Solanaceae): Insights into the genetic variation, phylogenetic relationship and polyploid speciation'.
3. We also upload the CDS sequences and gff3 annotation files used in this article.
